A recent study revealed that a sleep deficit over just five nights can harm heart function and increase the risk of cardiovascular disease and death.
Chronic sleep deprivation not only affects mood but also stresses the heart.
Research suggests that insufficient sleep is linked to cardiovascular issues, especially for early risers.
Athletes and college students often overlook the importance of adequate sleep.
Lack of sleep can impair memory and lead to weight gain.
Sleep disturbances in children and older adults are common.
Addressing sleep problems is crucial for overall health and well-being, especially in preventing cardiovascular issues and substance abuse.
